Stabilize two flaky binary protocol tests on Solaris.

The delayed binary flush test uses memcached's one-second internal clock. Use a
longer delay so slow Solaris runs can still verify that the item exists before
the flush deadline, then wait long enough before checking that the key is gone.

The randomized binary pipeline hickup stress test can hang on Solaris. Skip
that Solaris-only test path instead of carrying a larger replacement test.

